Linter:
> A new circular dependency in the form of "rpc/blockchain -> rpc/net -> rpc/blockchain" appears to have been introduced.

@MarcoFalke any thoughts on how to avoid that? I could move this new RPC method to `rpc/net`, or maybe the `EnsurePeerman` and `EnsureConnman` helpers should be in their own file?

Yesterdays PR Review Club covered this PR, thanks everyone! https://bitcoincore.reviews/20295

Rebased and addressed feedback.

@jnewbery in the use case I have in mind the node already has the header. We could always add a `getheaderfrompeer` RPC method if anyone needs it, though that seems a bit tedious to use. Alternative we can later expand `getblockfrompeer` to be smart about fetching

